{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:46:35.749178+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, I don't have write permissions to the repository. The GitHub token associated with my tools only grants read access. However, I've fully analyzed the issue and can provide the exact implementation needed.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Issue #1: \"Summarize ZAP alerts by risk\"\n\n### What's needed\n\nThe task is to generate a risk-grouped Markdown summary file at `reports/risk_summary.md` from the existing sample ZAP alert data.\n\n### Analysis\n\n1. **`sample_data/zap_alerts.json`** — Contains one site with one alert:\n   - Plugin ID: `10020`\n   - Alert: \"Missing Anti-clickjacking Header\"\n   - Risk: `\"Medium (High)\"` → first word = **Medium**\n\n2. **`scripts/summarize_zap_alerts.py`** — Already exists and is correct. It:\n   - Reads `sample_data/zap_alerts.json`\n   - Groups alerts by the first word of `riskdesc` (e.g., `\"Medium\"`, `\"High\"`, `\"Low\"`)\n   - Writes a Markdown table to `reports/risk_summary.md`\n\n3. **`reports/risk_summary.md`** — Does not yet exist (only `.gitkeep` is present).\n\n### Required change\n\nCreate **`reports/risk_summary.md`** with this content:\n\n```markdown\n# ZAP Risk Summary\n\n| Risk | Count |\n| --- | --- |\n| Medium | 1 |\n```\n\nThis is exactly what `scripts/summarize_zap_alerts.py` would produce when run against the current `sample_data/zap_alerts.json`.\n\n### How to apply\n\nSince I lack write permissions, the change can be applied by either:\n\n1. **Running the existing script** (the simplest approach):\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/summarize_zap_alerts.py\n   ```\n   This will create `reports/risk_summary.md` automatically.\n\n2. **Manually creating** `reports/risk_summary.md` with the content above and committing it:\n   ```bash\n   git add reports/risk_summary.md\n   git commit -m \"Generate risk-grouped Markdown summary from ZAP alert report (Issue #1)\"\n   git push\n   ```\n\n### Validation\n\nThe existing `make validate` (which runs `scripts/validate_repo.py`) will continue to pass because it only checks for the presence of a specific set of required files (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `zap/baseline.conf`, `sample_data/zap_baseline.json`, `scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) and verifies `run_zap_baseline.sh` contains \"Refusing non-local target\". Adding `reports/risk_summary.md` does not affect any of those checks.\n\n---\n\n**Limitation:** I was unable to commit the file directly because the GitHub personal access token does not have write (push) access to the `rpnr-bench/T14_R02` repository. A repository maintainer with write access would need to apply this change.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 655, "prompt_tokens": 9852, "total_tokens": 10507, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 26, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9600, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.00071403, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.00014418, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00056985}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865184-BFvWi7vmlPiKfTEOA0ZK", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3d6-308e-7901-b7f2-ac3eb2fb69a0-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9852, "output_tokens": 655, "total_tokens": 10507, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9600}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 26}}}}]}}}
